CBRE as the exclusive sales agent are pleased to present to market 527 King Street, Newtown. The property is a two-storey mixed use retail investment ideally positioned on one of Newtown’s major thoroughfare’s just 4.8km* from Sydney CBD. The ground floor retail is occupied by Project Snail, a popular  wood and clay design studio who occupy the space until November of 2022, with an option of a further two years generating approximately $49,157.53* In net annual income. The first floor comprises a charming residential apartment boasting three generous bedrooms, stylish wood flooring and an extraordinary skylight drenching the unit in natural sunlight. Additionally, the property enjoys a substantial rear courtyard and rear lane access to Alice Street offering onsite car accommodation. 

The property is sensationally situated amongst the commercial heart of Newtown in a gentrifying market, affording great vehicular and pedestrian exposure. The central location affords easy access to surrounding amenity including Newtown High School of Performing Arts (550m*), Newtown Train Station (650m*), Sydney Park (700m*) and Enmore Theatre (800m*). 527 King Street, Newtown offers the opportunity to live and work from home, to capture a secure investment opportunity, or redevelop (STCA).

527 King Street, Newtown benefits from the following key attributes:

•Ground floor retail leased to popular and highly rated tenant generating approximately $49,157.53* Net annual income 
•Secure lease to Project Snail until November of 2022 with options to 2024. 
 •Tenant pays 100% of water rates and trade waste  
•Generous total site area of 240sqm*
•Building area: 150sqm*
•Characterful three-bedroom residence located on the first floor  
•Convenient rear lane access with secure lock up car parking 
•Prominent main road location providing substantial foot and vehicle exposure
•Situated in the commercial heart of Newtown surrounded by fantastic local amenity
•650m* from Newtown Train Station 
•Opportunity to live and work from home, capture a secure investment opportunity, or redevelop (STCA)

527 King Street, Newtown will be sold via an online Public Auction at auctionWORKS on Tuesday 5 October 2021 at 10:30am (registration, livestream & online bidding will be available)

Inspections to be held by appointment as per COVID-19 Greater Sydney restriction requirements. Please enquire directly with the exclusive agents to arrange a private viewing.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approx.

CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 255 King Street, Newtown. This three-storey freehold building comprises two residential units and 50% of the ground floor retail shop, tenanted by the multi-award winning restaurant, The Italian Bowl. Situated in the heart of Newtown along the bustling King Street and leased to one of the suburb’s most iconic eateries, the property is a secure investment in Sydney’s rapidly growing Inner West.

255 King Street, Newtown benefits from the following key attributes: 

-	Two double storey residential units plus 50% of the ground floor retail shop
-	Tenanted by The Italian Bowl, winner of multiple awards including ‘Best Restaurant in the Inner West’ in the Inner West Local Business Awards 
-	NLA: 259sqm*
